      "type": "text",
      "text": "Note that we defined the term `ε1` to clarify that we use of $x/2$ in assumption `(i)`.\n\nNow we have derived that both $(x ≤ 0)$ and $¬ (x ≤ 0)$. To show a contradiction in Waterproof, you need to proof a statement $P$ and its negation $¬P$. Then you can finish the proof as follows."
